obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (10935)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10935&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the ^2[Petroleum and Minerals`
  line `Pipelines] (Acquisition of Right of User in Land) Act, 1962.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It applies in the first instance to the whole of the States of West Bengal, Bihar, Uttar-Pradesh and`
  line `Gujarat and the Union territory of Delhi, and the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, declare that this Act shall also apply to such other State of Union territory and with effect from`
  line `such date as may be specified in that notification and thereupon the provisions of this Act shall apply to`
  line `that State or Union territory accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Petroleum Pipelines" ( w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (10936)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1977, s. 4 (w.e.f. 3-2-1977)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10936&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "competent authority" means any person or authority authorised by the Central Government,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, to perform the functions of the competent authority under this`
  line `Act ^1[and different persons or authorities may be authorised to perform all or any of the functions of`
  line `the competent authority under this Act in the same area or different areas specified in the`
  line notification;]
  line
  line `(b) "corporation" means any body corporate established under any Central, Provincial or State`
  line `Act, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a company formed and registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956); and`
  line
  line `(ii) a company formed and registered under any law relating to companies formerly in force in`
  line `any part of India;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) "minerals" have the meanings assigned to them in the Mines Act, 1952 (35 of 1952), and`
  line `include mineral oils and stowing sand but do not include petroleum;]`
  line
  line `(c) "petroleum" has the same meaning as in the Petroleum Act, 1934 (30 of 1934), and includes`
  line `natural gas and refinery gas;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (10937)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Publication of notification for acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10937&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it appears to the Central Government`
  line `that it is necessary in the public interest that for the transport of petroleum ^1[or any mineral] from one`
  line `locality to another locality pipelines may be laid by that Government or by any State Government or a`
  line `corporation and that for the purpose of laying such pipelines it is necessary to acquire the right of user in any land under which such pipelines may be laid, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare`
  line `its intention to acquire the right of user therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under sub-section (1) shall give a brief description of the land.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority shall cause the substance of the notification to be published at such`
  line `places and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (10938)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to enter, survey, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `5 Ins. by Act 13 of 1977, s. 6 (w.e.f. 3-2-1977)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10938&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On the issue of a notification under sub-section (1) of section 3, it`
  line `shall be lawful for any person authorised by the Central Government or by the State Government or the`
  line `corporation which proposes to lay pipelines ^5`
  line `or any mineral, and his servants and workmen.`
  line `(a) to enter upon and survey and take levels of any land specified in the notification;`
  line `(b) to dig or bore into the sub-soil;`
  line `(c) to set out the intended line of work;`
  line `(d) to mark such levels, boundaries and line by placing marks and cutting trenches;`
  line `(e) where otherwise survey cannot be completed and levels taken and the boundaries and line`
  line `marked, to cut down and clear away any part of any standing crop, fence or jungle; and`
  line `(f) to do all other acts necessary to ascertain whether pipelines can be laid under the land:`
  line `Provided that where exercising any power under this section, such person or any servant or workmen`
  line `of such person shall cause as little damage or injury as possible to such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (10939)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Hearing of Objections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10939&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person interested in the land may, within twenty-one days from`
  line `the date of the notification under sub-section (1) of section 3, object to the laying of the pipelines under`
  line `the land.`
  line
  line `(2) Every objection under sub-section (1) shall be made to the competent authority in writing and`
  line `shall set out the grounds thereof and the competent authority shall give the objector an opportunity of`
  line `being heard either in person of by a legal practitioner and may, after hearing all such objections and after`
  line `making such further inquiry, if any, as that authority thinks necessary, by order either allow or disallow`
  line `the objections.`
  line
  line `(3) Any order made by the competent authority under sub-section (2) shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (10940)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Declaration of acquisition of right of user.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10940&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where no objections under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 5 have been made to the competent authority within the period specified therein or where the`
  line `competent authority has disallowed the objections under sub-section (2) of that section, that authority`
  line `shall, as soon as may be ^1[either make a report in respect of the land described in the notification under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3, or make different reports in respect of different parcels of such land, to the`
  line `Central Government containing his recommendations on the objections, together with the record of the`
  line `proceedings held by him, for the decision of that Government] and upon receipt of such report the Central`
  line `Government shall ^2[, if satisfied that such land is required for laying any pipeline for the transport of`
  line `petroleum or any mineral,] declare, by notification in the Official Gazette, that the right of user in the land`
  line `for laying the pipelines should be acquired.`
  line `^2[and different declarations may be made from time to time in`
  line `respect of different parcels of the land described in the notification issued under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `3, irrespective of whether one report or different reports have been made by the competent authority`
  line `under this section].`
  line
  line `(2) On the publication of the declaration under sub-section (1), the right of user ^3[in the land specified`
  line `therein] shall vest absolutely in the Central Government free from all encumbrances.`
  line
  line `(3) Where in respect of any land, a notification has been issued under sub-section (1) of section 3 but`
  line `^4[no declaration in respect of any parcel of land covered by that notification has been published under this`
  line `section] within a period of one year from the date of that notification, that notification shall cases to have`
  line `effect on the expiration of that period.`
  line
  line `^5[(3A) No declaration in respect of any land covered by a notification issued under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3, published after the commencement of the Petroleum Pipelines (Acquisition of Right of User in`
  line `Land) Amendment Act, 1977, shall be made after the expiry of three years from the date of such`
  line publication.]
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Central Government may, on such`
  line `terms and conditions as it may think fit to impose, direct by order in writing, that the right of user in the`
  line `land for laying the pipelines shall, instead of vesting in the Central Government vest, either on the date of`
  line `publication of the declaration or, on such other date as may be specified in the direction, in the State`
  line `Government or the corporation proposing to lay the pipelines and thereupon the right of such user in the`
  line `land shall, subject to the terms and conditions so imposed, vest in that State Government or corporation,`
  line `as the case may be, free from all encumbrances.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "submit a report accordingly to the Central Government" (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 1977, s. 7, for "in the land" (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "no declaration under this section has been published", (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (10941)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Central Government or State Government or corporation to lay pipelines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10941&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `right of user in any land has vested in the Central Government or in any State Government or corporation`
  line `under section 6`
  line
  line `(i) it shall be lawful for any person authorised by the Central Government or such State`
  line `Government or corporation as the case may be, and his servants and workmen to enter upon the land`
  line `and lay pipelines or to do any other act necessary for the laying of pipelines:`
  line
  line `Provided that no pipeline shall be laid under`
  line
  line `(a) any land which, immediately before the date of the notification under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3, was used for residential purposes;`
  line
  line `(b) any land on which there stands any permanent structure which was in existence`
  line `immediately before the said date;`
  line
  line `(c) any land which is appurtenant to a dwelling house; or`
  line
  line `(d) any land at a depth which is less than one metre from the surface ^1***;`
  line
  line `^2[(ia) for laying pipelines for the transport of petroleum, it shall be lawful for any person`
  line `authorised by the Central Government or such State Government or corporation to use such`
  line `land for laying pipelines for transporting any mineral and where the right of user in any land`
  line `has so vested for laying pipelines for transporting any mineral, it shall be lawful for such`
  line `person to use such land for laying pipelines for transporting petroleum or any other mineral;`
  line and.]
  line
  line `(ii) such land shall be used only for laying the pipelines and for maintaining, examining,`
  line `repairing, altering or removing any such pipelines or for doing any other act necessary for`
  line `any of the aforesaid purposes or for the utilisation of such pipelines.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises with regard to any matter referred to in paragraph (b) or paragraph (c) of the`
  line `proviso to clause (i) of sub-section (1), the dispute shall be referred to the competent authority whose`
  line `decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (10942)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to enter land for inspection, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10942&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `For maintaining, examining, repairing, altering or`
  line `removing any pipelines, or for doing any other act necessary for the utilisation of the pipelines or for the`
  line `making of any inspection or measurement for any of the aforesaid purposes, any person authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government, the State Government or the corporation, as the case may be, may,`
  line `after giving reasonable notice to the occupier of the land under which the pipelines has been laid, enter`
  line `therein with such workmen and assistants as may be necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where such person is satisfied that an emergency exists no such notice shall be`
  line `necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, while exercising any powers under this section, such person or any workmen or`
  line `assistant of such person, shall cause as little damage or injury as possible to such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (10943)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Restrictions regarding the use of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1977, s. 9 (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10943&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner or occupier of theland with respect to`
  line `which a declaration has been made under sub-section (1) of section 6, shall be entitled to use the land for`
  line `the purpose for which such land was put to use immediately before the date of the notification under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3:`
  line
  line `Provided that, such owner or occupier shall not after the declaration under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6--`
  line
  line `(i) construct any building or any other structure;`
  line
  line `(ii) construct or excavate any tank, well, reservoir or dam; or`
  line
  line `(iii) plant any tree,`
  line
  line `on that land.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner or occupier of the land under which any pipelines has been laid shall not do any act or`
  line `permit any act to be done which will or is likely to cause any damage in any manner whatsoever to the`
  line pipeline.
  line
  line `^1[(3) Where the owner or occupier of the land with respect to which a declaration has been made`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 6,--`
  line
  line `(a) constructs any building or any other structure, or`
  line
  line `(b) constructs or excavates any well, tank, reservoir or dam, or`
  line
  line `(c) plants any tree,`
  line
  line `on that land, the Court of the District Judge within the local limits of whose jurisdiction such land is`
  line `situate may, on an application made to it by the competent authority and after holding such inquiry as it`
  line `may deem fit, cause the building, structure, reservoir, dam or tree to be removed or the well or tank to be`
  line `filled up, and the costs of such removal or filling up shall be recoverable from such owner or occupier in`
  line `the same manner as if the order for the recovery of such costs were a decree made by that Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (10944)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Compensation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10944&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in the exercise of the powers conferred by section 4, section 7 or`
  line `section 8 by any person, any damage, loss or injury is sustained by any person interested in the land under`
  line `which the pipeline is proposed to be, or is being, or has been laid, the Central Government, the State`
  line `Government or the corporation , as the case may be , shall be liable to pay compensation to such person`
  line `for such damage, loss or injury , the amount of which shall be determined by the competent authority in`
  line `the first instance.`
  line
  line `(2) If the amount of compensation determined by the competent authority under sub-section (1) is not`
  line `acceptable to either of the parties, the amount of compensation shall, on application by either of the`
  line `parties to the District Judge within the limits of whose jurisdiction the land or any part thereof is situated,`
  line `be determined by that District Judge.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority or the District Judge while determining the compensation under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be, shall have due regard to the damage or loss`
  line `sustained by any person interested in the land by reason of--`
  line
  line `(i) the removal of trees of standing crops, if any, on the land while exercising the power under`
  line `section 4, section 7 or section 8;`
  line
  line `(ii) the temporary severance of the land under which the pipeline has been laid from other lands`
  line `belonging to, or in the occupation of, such person; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any injury to any other property, whether movable or immovable , or the earnings of such`
  line `persons caused in any other manner:`
  line
  line `Provided that in determining the compensation no account shall be taken of any structure or other`
  line `improvement made in the land after the date of the notification under sub-section (1) of section 3.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the right of user of any land has vested in the Central Government, the State Government`
  line `or the corporation , the Central Government, the State Government or the corporation , as the case may`
  line `be, shall, in addition to the compensation, if any, payable under sub-section (1), be liable to pay to the`
  line `owner and to any other person whose right of enjoyment in that land has been affected in any manner`
  line `whatsoever by reason of such vesting, compensation calculated at ten per cent. of the market value of that`
  line `land on the date of the notification under sub-section (1) of section 3.`
  line
  line `(5) The market value of the land on the said date shall be determined by the competent authority and`
  line `if the value so determined by that authority is not acceptable to either of the parties, it shall, on`
  line `application by either of the parties to the District Judge referred to in sub-section (2), be determined by`
  line `that District Judge.`
  line
  line `(6) The decision of the District Judge under sub-section (2) or sub-section (5) shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (10945)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Deposit and payment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10945&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount of compensation determined under`
  line `section 10 shall be deposited by the Central Government, the State Government or the corporation, as the`
  line `case may be, with the competent authority within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) If the amount of compensation is not deposited within the time prescribed under sub-section (1),`
  line `the Central Government, the State Government or the corporation, as the case may be, shall be liable to`
  line `pay interest thereon at the rate of six per cent. per annum from the date on which the compensation had to`
  line `be deposited till the date of the actual deposit.`
  line
  line `(3) As soon as may be after the compensation has been deposited under sub-section (1) the competent`
  line `authority shall, on behalf of the Central Government the State Government or the corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, pay the compensation to the persons entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) Where several persons claim to be interested in the amount of compensation deposited under`
  line `sub-section (1), the competent authority shall determined the persons who in its opinion are entitled to`
  line `receive the compensation and the amount payable to each of them.`
  line
  line `(5) If any dispute arises as to the apportionment of the compensation or any part thereof or as to the`
  line `persons to whom the same or any part thereon is payable, the competent authority shall refer the dispute`
  line `to the decision of the District Judge within the limits of whose jurisdiction the land or any part thereof is`
  line `situated and the decision of the District Judge thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (10946)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Competent authority to have certain powers of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10946&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority shall`
  line `have, for the purposes of this Act, all the powers of a civil court while trying a suit under the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commission for examination of witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (10947)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10947&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of this Act or any rule or notification made or issued thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government, the competent`
  line `authority or any State Government, or corporation for any damage, loss or injury caused or likely to be`
  line `caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule`
  line `or notification made or issued there under.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (10948)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10948&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no civil`
  line `court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter which the competent authority is empowered by or`
  line `under this Act to determine and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of`
  line `any action taken or proposed to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (10949)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2012, s. 2, for sections 15 and 16 (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10949&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Penalty.--(1) Whoever wilfully obstructs any person in doing any of the acts authorised by`
  line `section 4 or section 7 or section 8 or wilfully fills up, destroys, damages or displaces any trench or mark`
  line `made under section 4 or wilfully does any act prohibited under section 9, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever wilfully makes or causes to make any unauthorised connection with or removes,`
  line `destroys, damages or displaces any pipeline laid under section 7, or wilfully inserts any device to extract`
  line `petroleum product or minerals from such pipeline, or wilfully disrupts supplies being made through the`
  line `pipeline, shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person convicted of an offence under sub-section (2) is again convicted of an offence under`
  line `the same provision, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for the second and for every`
  line `subsequent offence for a term which shall not be less than three years but which may extend to ten years:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than three years.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever, with the intent to cause or knowing that he is likely to cause damage to or destruction of`
  line `any pipeline laid under section 7, causes by fire, explosive substance or otherwise damage to the pipeline`
  line `being used for transportation of petroleum products, crude oil or gas with the intent to commit sabotage or`
  line `with the knowledge that such act is so imminently dangerous that it may in all probability cause death of`
  line `any person or such bodily injury likely to cause death of any person, shall be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment which shall not be less than ten years but may extend to imprisonment for life or death.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (10950)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Certain offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2012, s. 2, for sections 15 and 16 (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10950&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Certain offences to be cognizable.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an offence falling under sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 15`
  line `shall be deemed to be cognizable and non-bailable within the meaning of that Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (10951)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 17
  title `Burden of proof in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2012, s. 2, for sections 15 and 16 (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10951&sectionno=16A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[16A. Burden of proof in certain cases.--Where any petroleum product together with any tool,`
  line `vehicle or any item used in committing any such offence under sub-section (2) or sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 15 are seized under this Act in the reasonable belief that such petroleum product has been stolen`
  line `from the pipeline laid under section 7, the burden of proving that they are not stolen property shall be, in`
  line `case where such seizure is made from the possession of any person,--`
  line
  line `(i) on the person from whose possession the property was seized, and`
  line
  line `(ii) on the person who claims to be the owner thereof, if any person other than the person from`
  line `whose possession the stolen property was seized.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_b:
  sectionId (10952)
  sectionNo 16B
  orderNo 18
  title `Presumption regarding property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2012, s. 2, for sections 15 and 16 (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10952&sectionno=16B&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[16B. Presumption regarding property.--When any proceeding taken under this Act, or in`
  line `consequence of anything done under this Act, a question arises as to whether any petroleum product is the`
  line `property of the corporation, the Court shall presume, unless the contrary is shown, that such petroleum`
  line `product belongs to the corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_c:
  sectionId (10953)
  sectionNo 16C
  orderNo 19
  title `Provisions as to bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2012, s. 2, for sections 15 and 16 (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10953&sectionno=16C&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_16_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[16C. Provisions as to bail.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no person accused of an offence punishable under sub-section (4) of section`
  line `15 shall, if in custody, be released on bail or on his own bond unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the Public Prosecutor has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such`
  line `release; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the court is satisfied that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not likely to`
  line `commit any offence while on bail.`
  line
  line `(2) The limitations on granting of bail specified in sub-section (1) are in addition to the limitations`
  line `under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law for the time being in force on`
  line `granting of bail.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the special powers of the High Court`
  line `regarding bail under section 439 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_d:
  sectionId (10954)
  sectionNo 16D
  orderNo 20
  title `Section 438 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 not to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2012, s. 2, for sections 15 and 16 (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10954&sectionno=16D&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_16_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[16D. Section 438 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 not to apply.--Nothing in section 438`
  line `of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply in relation to any case involving the`
  line `arrest of any person on an accusation of having committed an offence punishable under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 15.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (10955)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10955&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the ^1[provisions] of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particulars and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the places at which and the manner in which the substance of the notification may be`
  line `published under sub -section (3) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the time within which and the manner in which the amount of compensation may be deposited`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 11.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each Houses`
  line `of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if ^1[before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however that any such modification or annulment`
  line `shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule .`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 1977, s. 10, for "purposes" (w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1977, s. 10, for "before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the successive sessions aforesaid"`
  line `(w.e.f. 3-2-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (10956)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318&sectionId=10956&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_50_00004_196250_1517807322318
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to and`
  line `not in derogation of any other law for the time being in force relating to acquisition of land.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
